<h2>About</h2>
<p>
Dr. A.P.J Abdul Kalam was one of India's most respected scientists and the 11th President of India.
He played a major role in India's missile development and space research programs.
He was widely known as the "Missile Man of India".
</p>
</div>

<!-- Achievements -->
<div class="section" id="achievements">
<h2>Achievements</h2>
<ul>
<li>Key role in Pokhran-II nuclear tests.</li>
<li>Developed India's Agni and Prithvi missiles.</li>
<li>11th President of India (2002–2007).</li>
<li>Awarded Bharat Ratna in 1997.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<!-- Inspiration -->
<div class="section" id="inspiration">
<h2>Inspiration</h2>
<p>
Dr. Kalam inspired millions of students through his speeches, books,
and dedication to education. His famous quote:
<b>"Dream, Dream, Dream. Dreams transform into thoughts and thoughts result in action."</b>
</p>
